ELEVATED CARDIAC TROPONIN LEVELS ARE NOT SPECIFIC FOR THE DIAGNOSIS OF ACS OR ACUTE SPONTANEOUS MYOCARDIAL INFARCTION (TYPE 1 MI).
MYOCARDIAL STRAIN FROM NON-ACS CONDITIONS (TYPE 2 MI) SUCH AS SEPSIS, CONGESTIVE HEART FAILURE, MYOCARDITIS, DRUG TOXICITY, PULMONARY EMBOLISM, HYPOXIA, AND TRAUMA CAN BE ASSOCIATED WITH ELEVATED TROPONIN LEVELS.
